news.title: Delhi: NDMC property tax mop-up past Rs 1,000 crore, half of MCD
news.para: NDMC’s total collection from property tax stood at Rs 933 crore in FY 2022-23, Rs 951 crore in FY 2021-22 and Rs 690 crore in FY 2020-21.

news.title: China Vanke posts 50.6% drop in 2023 core profit
news.para: Investors have been dumping China Vanke's shares and bonds in the past few weeks, triggering a rare central government directive to help the Shenzhen-based developer beat a liquidity crisis.

news.title: BMC issues notice to Mumbai metro contractors over Rs 370 crore property tax default
news.para: The civic body said that as Metro works are ongoing at several locations in the city, the contractors are contractually liable to pay the property tax of the casting yard plot.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body postpones sale of 22 plots due to Lok Sabha election
news.para: ​Before the code was enacted, the AMC had already announced the public auction of these plots, with a cumulative base price of Rs 2,250 crore.

news.title: Jaipur development body, JMC demolishes five illegal colonies
news.para: Officials said around 150 places on both sides of the footpath and road were illegally occupied by squatters who put up carts, tarpaulins, hoardings, signboards, iron angles, platforms, tin shaded tables and chairs among others.

news.title: Kochi civic body to let 'total' construction in risk zones prone to flooding
news.para: Kochi corporation master plan, that has been approved by town planning department, envisages giving approval for total construction in the areas instead of the 50% approved earlier.

news.title: Madurai civic body nets 77% property tax in FY24
news.para: Madurai corporation has collected Rs 223 crore out of the targeted Rs 352 crore, including tax arrears, until March. This was 15% more than that collected in the previous fiscal when the corporation netted Rs 192 crore of which arrears accounted for Rs 35 crore.

news.title: China: Property developers' 2023 results hit by sector downturn
news.para: China's property sector, a pillar of the economy, has lurched from one crisis to another since 2021 after a regulatory crackdown on high leverage among developers triggered a liquidity crisis.

news.title: Blackstone plans to add $25 billion in India private equity assets over five years
news.para: Blackstone also intends to bring on 20 more investment professionals to its asset management business in India and double its office space in Nariman Point in downtown Mumbai, according to its head of private equity in Asia, Amit Dixit.

news.title: Property registrations, revenue hit three-year high in Maharashtra
news.para: “Maharashtra has recorded more than 27 lakh property registrations this financial year so far, resulting in a revenue of about Rs 48,000 crore,” a senior official from the state property registration department said.

news.title: Kolkata-based Jain Group to invest Rs 500 crore in hospitality business
news.para: It has collaborated with Sarovar Hotels Pvt Ltd to start a new hotel in Rajarhat in the next four months. As part of the deal, the Jain Group has shelled out around Rs 120 crore for the project.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA recovers Rs 160 crore from builders
news.para: The highest number of warrants was issued in suburban Mumbai district. A total of 434 warrants have been issued for 114 projects to recover Rs 298 crore.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance to invest Rs 25 crore for 5% stake in RDCL
news.para: RDCL is aimed at revitalising the residential mortgage-backed securities (RMBS) market and unlocking its potential for financing affordable housing, according to a statement by IIFL.

news.title: Delhi: DDA invite bids for demolition of Signature View Apartments
news.para: The apartment complex, built in 2007-09 with 336 MIG and HIG flats, has some construction issues and has been up for demolition by the DDA.

news.title: Macrotech Developers to raise Rs 125 crore through issue of debentures
news.para: According to a regulatory filing on Thursday, the executive committee of the Board of Directors of Macrotech Developers has approved the allotment of 12,500 non-convertible debentures of Rs 1 lakh each aggregating to Rs 125 crore.

news.title: China's ICBC to support stabilisation of property market
news.para: The comments were made by Wang Jingwu, a vice president at the world's largest lender, at a press conference held a day after its annual results were published. Wang did not specify what kind of support ICBC would provide.

news.title: Fitch Ratings downgrades China's Longfor Group to 'junk'
news.para: Fitch downgraded Longfor to 'BB+' from 'BBB-', which was the last notch for the investment-grade ratings, adding a negative outlook.

news.title: Adani family infuses Rs 6,661 crore in Ambuja Cements
news.para: The fund's infusion will be instrumental for the cement business of the Adani group, which has plans to enhance its capacity to 140 million tonnes per annum by 2028, according to a statement from billionaire Gautam Adani-owned Ambuja Cements.

news.title: S&P cuts Sweden's SBB rating to selective default
news.para: The property group, which has been scrambling to cut its debt mountain, recently repaid some bondholders a fraction of what they were owed in a tender offer.

news.title: Gujarat HC directs state government to take possession of APMC’s hotel
news.para: The bench of Chief Justice Sunita Agarwal and Justice Aniruddha Mayee further ordered action against erring officials and APMC members responsible for the construction of the luxurious hotel.
